 from the integrated power of the\nmagnetic reconnection events, we evaluated the time-variability from a power\nspectral density analysis, obtaining a good agreement with the observations in\nthe GeV band. This suggests that turbulent fast magnetic reconnection driven by\nkink instability can be a possible process behind the high energy emission\nvariability phenomena observed in blazars.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 6 Nov 2020 23:40:22 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 3 Mar 2021 02:12:19 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 25 Mar 2021 20:29:04 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-05-19"}
